snippet.textDisplay:
On the 1400$ pricing one of the more underated and exclusive features of the S20 Ultra is how they were able to put in all the main 5G connectivity options including Sub-6 (Ghz) and Millimetre Wave all in one compact device.
For this it's the 1st real mainstream 5G phone, will inspire copying years down the road leading to more adoption.

The other / budget 5G phones don't have this, plus I guess it's what Apple were waiting for - that its forthcoming 5G phones will have a near if not fully similar implementation. Others do the primary R&D, they innovate seek to refine it then charge extra for the patents they have to include.

I further guess another of the main reasons of the phones pricing is it can handle many 4G bands as well. Noticeably budget phones i.e. for Xiaomi etc. with similar but cheaper Qualcomm Snapdragon chip variants only handle a few select bands for particular regions.

+ Android phones depreciate real quick. This one may hold value for longer, given its future proofed hardware outlook. The production cost may be significantly recouped if not forked out to other Samsung models.
